        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 5:55PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 7 miles south of Paris
Landing State Park to 7 miles southeast of Springville to near
Huntingdon. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntingdon, Camden, Bruceton, Vale, Springville, Hollow Rock, Big
Sandy, Mansfield, Haigler Ridge, Manleyville, Old Springville, Spring
Creek, Crews Store, Ephesus, Nathan Bedford Forrest State Park, and
Big Sandy Unit Tennessee National Wildlife Refuge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
